                  <li class="program-course">
            <a href="/study/2014-2015/courses/esys-200" class="program-course-title">
              ESYS 200 Earth System Processes (3 credits)              <!---->            </a>
            <div class="program-course-description">
              <div class="program-course-description-inner">
                <div id="node-25438" class=" clearfix">
  
  
  
  <div class="meta">
    <p>Offered by: Earth &amp; Planetary Sciences (<a href="/study/2014-2015/node/615">Faculty of Science</a>)</p>
      </div>

  <div class="content">
    <h3>Overview</h3>

    <p>
      Earth System Science              : Complex interactions among the atmosphere, biosphere, geosphere and hydrosphere. Biological, chemical and physical processes within and between each "sphere" that extend over spatial scales ranging from microns to the size of planetary orbits and that span time scales from fractions of a second to billions of years.          </p>

    <p class="catalog-terms">
      Terms:              Winter 2015          </p>

    <p class="catalog-instructors">
      Instructors:                        Bernhard Lehner, Eric Douglas Galbraith (Winter)                  </p>

    
          <ul class="catalog-notes">
              <li>Winter</li>
              <li>3 hours lecture</li>
              <li>Prerequisite(s): ENVR 200 or permission of instructor.</li>
            </ul>
      </div>

  </div> <!-- /.node -->
              </div>
            </div>
