            <div class="program-course-description">
              <div class="program-course-description-inner">
                <div id="node-18534" class=" clearfix">
  
  
  
  <div class="meta">
    <p>Offered by: Atmospheric &amp; Oceanic Sciences (<a href="/study/2014-2015/node/615">Faculty of Science</a>)</p>
      </div>

  <div class="content">
    <h3>Overview</h3>

    <p>
      Atmospheric &amp; Oceanic Sciences              : Solar and terrestrial radiation. Interactions of molecules, aerosols, clouds, and precipitation with radiation of various wavelengths. Radiative transfer through the clear and cloudy atmosphere. Radiation budgets. Satellite and ground-based measurements. Climate implications.          </p>

    <p class="catalog-terms">
      Terms:              Winter 2015          </p>

    <p class="catalog-instructors">
      Instructors:                        Yi Huang (Winter)                  </p>

    
          <ul class="catalog-notes">
              <li>Prerequisites (Undergraduates): ATOC 315, MATH 314, and MATH 315, or permission of instructor.</li>
              <li>Restriction: Not open to students who have taken ATOC 620.</li>
            </ul>
      </div>

  </div> <!-- /.node -->
              </div>
            </div>
