                  <li class="program-course">
            <a href="/study/2014-2015/courses/atoc-541" class="program-course-title">
              ATOC 541 Synoptic Meteorology 2 (3 credits)              <!---->            </a>
            <div class="program-course-description">
              <div class="program-course-description-inner">
                <div id="node-18542" class=" clearfix">
  
  
  
  <div class="meta">
    <p>Offered by: Atmospheric &amp; Oceanic Sciences (<a href="/study/2014-2015/node/615">Faculty of Science</a>)</p>
      </div>

  <div class="content">
    <h3>Overview</h3>

    <p>
      Atmospheric &amp; Oceanic Sciences              : Analysis of current meteorological data. Quasi-geostrophic theory, including the omega equation, as it relates to extratropical cyclone and anticyclone development. Frontogenesis and frontal circulations in the lower and upper troposphere. Cumulus convection and its relationship to tropical and extratropical circulations. Diagnostic case study work.          </p>

    <p class="catalog-terms">
      Terms:              Winter 2015          </p>

    <p class="catalog-instructors">
      Instructors:                        Eyad Hashem Atallah (Winter)                  </p>

    
          <ul class="catalog-notes">
              <li>Winter</li>
              <li>2 hours lecture; 2 hours laboratory</li>
              <li>Prerequisite (Undergraduate): ATOC 412 and ATOC 540 or permission of instructor.</li>
            </ul>
      </div>

  </div> <!-- /.node -->
